#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:1
msgid "Tabs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:3
msgid ""
"Tabs are good way to organize content, where the reader has choice they can "
"make (usually based on their environment)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:5
msgid ""
"While Sphinx does not provide tabs out-of-the-box, it is achievable by using "
"extensions with Sphinx. Furo works well with the following extensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:7
msgid "[sphinx-inline-tabs]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:9
msgid ""
"This is a small package that provides one thing: good-looking tabs that work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:14
msgid ""
".. tab:: One\n"
"\n"
"    First.\n"
"\n"
".. tab:: Two\n"
"\n"
"    Second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:28 ../../../reference/tabs.md:47
msgid "First."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:32 ../../../reference/tabs.md:51
msgid "Second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:36
msgid ""
"```{tab} One\n"
"First.\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"```{tab} Two\n"
"Second.\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:33
msgid "[sphinx-design]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/tabs.md:35
msgid ""
"A wide ranging extension, providing many reusable components for site "
"content, including tabs."
msgstr ""

